AB  - Missing values, non-regular sampling censored data and departure from normality are common problems in the analysis of ecological or environmental time series. For over 20 years, in the scope of the National Basin Network in France, numerous water quality time series have been collected A method is proposed for the regularization of the series, the detection of trend changes and short-term forecasting, on the basis of the last detected trend, using a non-parametric regression. The method is applied to phosphates and nitrogen concentrations measured on the Sambre river (northern France).
