TI  - A STOCHASTIC-MODEL FOR ORDERED CATEGORICAL TIME-SERIES - APPLICATION TO PLANKTONIC ABUNDANCE DATA
T2  - ECOLOGICAL MODELLING
AB  - A Markov model for ordered categorical time series is developed. The model is written in terms of the cumulative probability function, conditionally on the observed past, and incorporates stochastic time-dependent covariates. We propose maximum likelihood estimation and hypothesis test procedures whose asymptotic properties are based on the assumption that the observed process is periodic. This approach is used to analyse a long-term series of semi-quantitative salp abundance data (Thalia democratica, a pelagic Tunicata), and to evaluate the influence on the salp population of hydrological covariates.
