TI  - STL statistical approach to analyze airborne pollen long-term trends
T2  - INTERNATIONAL WORK-CONFERENCE ON TIME SERIES (ITISE 2014)
CP  - 1st International Work-Conference on Time Series (ITISE)
AB  - Annual airborne pollen recorded in a place is usually strongly correlated with flowering intensity in that area and surroundings. It has been demonstrated that water availability is an important variable in flowering intensity. However, other parameters, mainly temperature and relative humidity, influence on plant reproductive development.
   The present study has been performed in the city of Cordoba (South Spain). It has been analyzed airborne pollen data during the period 1996-2010. Mediterranean climate is characterized by a high inter-annual variability in its meteorological patterns, showing climatic micro-cycles, alternating wet and dry periods. The selected statistical technique for extracting the trend component of pollen time series has been the seasonal decomposition procedure by Loess method (STL). STL decomposes long time series taking into account short term patterns. It has been also analyzed changes on land uses around the city (5000 m radius, 10000 m radius, 25000 m radius, 50000 m radius) during the period 1999 and 2007.
   Results show different trends depending on species. Some agronomical species, as Olea, show significant increasing trend, attributable to the increment on olive crop areas during last years. On the other hand, some taxa related with strong anthropic influence, i.e. Rumex, Plantago, Amaranthaceae or Parietaria, show significant decreasing trends that could be related with recent changes in urban planning, as the increase of urban land and decreasing on urban wastelands. In the same way, the crescent trend on species with ornamental use, as Platanus, Cupressus, Mirtus or Morus is well related with changes on urbanized land around pollen trap. The increase on rainfall during the first three months of the year has been better correlated with positive trend on Poaceae and Quercus airborne pollen. Urtica membranaceae is a nitrophilous specie whose positive trend may be related with the increase of heterogeneous agricultural areas and olive grove around the city. STL method has shown high effectiveness for extracting trend component of ecological time series, because the features of nature present a wide range of possibilities and it can change quickly at short term.
