TI  - Analysis of Long-Term Dynamics of a Vegetation Index at Sites of the Oil and Gas Complex with the Application of Satellite Data
T2  - PROCEEDINGS OF THE INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON ADVANCED MATERIALS WITH HIERARCHICAL STRUCTURE FOR NEW TECHNOLOGIES AND RELIABLE STRUCTURES 2019
CP  - International Conference on Advanced Materials with Hierarchical Structure for New Technologies and Reliable Structures
AB  - The use of satellite data for analyzing the dynamics of values of vegetation indices for vegetation of inaccessible territories of oil and gas fields of the Tomsk Oblast is considered. Satellite data are used to calculate the time series of the Enhanced Vegetation Index (EVI), which is a modified Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) with reduced sensitivity to atmospheric conditions. To analyze the EVI change, MOD13Q1 data with a spatial resolution of 250 m for the period from 2007 to 2017 are used. The average EVI values are calculated for the sites of five hydrocarbon deposits in the Tomsk Oblast: Archinskoye, Shinginskoye, Zapadno-Ostaninskoye, Yuzhno-Tabaganskoye, and Kazanskoye. The analysis of the dynamics of changes in average EVI values allows to determine the minimal and maximal values of the index for the sites under study, as well as to identify a trend of an increase in its values, which suggests a good non-depressed state of vegetation and an improvement in the ecological situation of the territories under study.
