TI  - Biocoenotic changes of the zooplankton in the German Bight: The possible effects of eutrophication and climate
T2  - ICES JOURNAL OF MARINE SCIENCE
CP  - ICES International Symposium on changes in the North Sea Ecosystem and Their Causes - Arhus 1975 Revisited
AB  - Meso- and macrozooplankton have been sampled in the German Eight since 1974. Inter-annual changes in the dynamics of selected species have been analysed in terms of mean annual abundance and timing of abundance maxima. Information on new immigrants is also presented. Possible causes of the observed changes, particularly in relation to nutrient availability and climatic signals, are discussed. (C) 1996 International Council for the Exploration of the Sea
